\ watchdog.kevo:\ A task which prints information about the tasks in the system\ -------------------------------------------------------------\ (c) Antero Taivalsaari 12.5.1992" ok.kevo" fromRoot CDDEFINED System not IF MKDIR System THENSystem CDDEFINED WatchDog IF endFrom THENMKDIR WatchDogWatchDog ADDS\ Define a foreground task with a window	REF watchTask	Prototypes.Concurrency.TerminalTask.new -> watchTask\ Set the window name	" Watchdog" watchTask.output.setTitle\ Define what the task should do : watchJob	BEGIN		page cr		taskingMode 		IF   ." Cooperative " 		ELSE ." Preemptive " 		THEN 		multitasking @ 		IF   ." multitasking" 		ELSE ." singletasking"		THEN cr cr		." Total number of tasks.: " #tasks . cr		." Number of active tasks: " #running . cr cr		." Free memory: " room . ." bytes"		checkSystemValidity \ perform system integrity checks		500 msecs  ( 5 seconds delay )	AGAIN ;	\ Assign behavior to the task	' watchJob watchTask.does \ Give the task a low priority 	watchTask.lowerPriority	watchTask.lowerPriority\ Activate the watchDog task	watchTask.activateENDADDS;